Popular nightclub owner and Instagram celebrity, Okechukwu popularly called ‘Cubana Chief Priest’ has been arrested by detectives attached to the Inspector General of Police Monitoring Unit. Okechukwu is the proprietor of posh nightclub, The Cubana with outlets on Lagos Island and Ikeja.
 
Top police sources at the Police Force Headquarters annex in Lagos told The Guardian that he is being held in custody for money laundering, reckless use of policemen and questionable lavish lifestyle.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .